HEADWORD: Scary
<hw>Sca"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>scare</ets> scraggy.]</ety> <def>Barren land having only a thin
coat of grass.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scary
<hw>Scar"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Scare</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Subject to sudden alarm.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. U. S.]</mark> <rj><au>Whittier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing fright; alarming.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scasely</ent>⟦br⟧
